value: Bred formerly in the forested area of North America from Great Bear Lake, northern Manitoba, James Bay, central Quebec and Nova Scotia, south to Kansas, Mississippi, Kentucky, West Virginia, Pennsylvania, and southern New England. Wintered from Arkansas and North Carolina south to Louisiana and Florida; casually to Cuba, the Valley of Mexico and Bermuda. Now extinct.
refer: Peter's Checklist of the Birds of the World

value: Forest, foraging in open country and cultivated lands adjacent to forest.

subcat_descr: Number of breeding attempts per year
